r North University Avenue on the southwest corner of campus, and is expected to open for revenue service with the system in early 2022.<ref name=\"RDF\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.redlandsdailyfacts.com/construction-begins-for-rail-connecting-redlands-to-san-bernardino|title=Construction begins for rail connecting Redlands to San Bernardino|work=Redlands Daily Facts|date=July 19, 2019}}</ref> {{as of|2017}} the University was planning to construct a [[transit village]] at the site via a [[public\u2013private partnership]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Emerson |first1=Sandra |title=How the University of Redlands is preparing for passenger rail service |url=https://www.redlandsdailyfacts.com/2017/09/28/how-the-university-of-redlands-is-preparing-for-passenger-rail-service/ |accessdate=18 December 2019 |agency=Redlands Daily Facts |date=28 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Metrolink (Southern California)}}\n{{California-railstation-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations scheduled to open in 2022]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Redlands, California]]\n[[Category:University of Redlands]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in California at university and college campuses]]\n[[Category:Future Metrolink (California) stations]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station\n| name                = University\n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = \n| symbol_location     = losangeles\n| symbol              = metrolink\n| type                = [[Arrow (commuter rail)|Arrow]] commuter rail station\n| image               = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| address             = N. University Ave.\n| borough             = [[Redlands, California]]\n| country             = \n| coordinates         = {{coord|34.058872|-117.165729|display=inline,title}}\n| owned               = \n| operator            = \n| line                = Redlands Subdivision\n| distance            = \n| platforms           = \n| tracks              = \n| train_operators     = \n| connections         = \n| structure           = \n| parking             = \n| bicycle             = \n| disabled            = \n| code                = \n| iata                =\n| zone                = \n| website             = \n| opening              = {{Start date|2022|df=y}}\n| electrified         =\n| passengers          = \n| pass_year           = \n| pass_rank           = \n| services            = {{Adjacent stations|system=Omnitrans|line=Arrow|left=Redlands\u2013Downtown}}\n| other_services      = \n}}\n'''University'''<ref name=Oct19timetable>{{cite web |title=Timetable |url=https://www.metrolinktrains.com/globalassets/schedules/singles_mlk_lft_alllines_19_10_14.pdf |website=Metrolink |publisher=SCRRA |accessdate=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Nero |first1=Mark |title=Groundbreaking Held For Redlands-To-San-Bernardino Rail Line |url=https://patch.com/california/redlands/groundbreaking-held-redlands-san-bernardino-rail-line |accessdate=18 December 2019 |agency=Patch |date=22 July 2019}}</ref> is a planned [[Arrow (commuter rail)|Arrow]] [[commuter rail]] [[terminal station]] that will serve the [[University of Redlands]]. It is planned to be located near North University Avenue on the southwest corner of campus, and is expected to open for revenue service with the system in early 2022.<ref name=\"RDF\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.redlandsdailyfacts.com/construction-begins-for-rail-connecting-redlands-to-san-bernardino|title=Construction begins for rail connecting Redlands to San Bernardino|work=Redlands Daily Facts|date=July 19, 2019}}</ref> {{as of|2017}} the University was planning to construct a [[transit village]] at the site via a [[public\u2013private partnership]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Emerson |first1=Sandra |title=How the University of Redlands is preparing for passenger rail service |url=https://www.redlandsdailyfacts.com/2017/09/28/how-the-university-of-redlands-is-preparing-for-passenger-rail-service/ |accessdate=18